Many real top-level commands are absent from docs/cli-reference.md and README.md (onboard, provider, channel, memory, session, workspace, subagents, delegate, plan, rig, runtime, tunnel, reset-agent, reset-workspace, otp-show, version, hardware, debug, benchmark, setup, watcher, ec-run, manifest, plus background/pair/rooms subcommand gaps). The doc currently says 'covers the common, user-facing commands'. Decision: which commands are public/support-supported vs internal/debug? Then document the public set. Found in docs-audit (lanes A-5, B-08).